com.paydiant.android.ui.service.userregistration

Class UserManagementListenerAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paydiant.android.ui.service.userregistration.UserManagementListenerAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IUserManagementListener

    public class UserManagementListenerAdapter
extends Object
implements IUserManagementListener
    This class provides an empty implementation for IUserManagementListener. Any classes that wants to use only a subset of the listener methods can override the relevant methods and use it as the interface implementation. 

      UserManagementListenerAdapter managementListenerAdapter = new UserManagementListenerAdapter() {
      @Override
      public void onValidateEmailSuccess() {
      }
      
      @Override
      public void onUserRegistrationError(PaydiantException exception) {
      }
 };
 iUserManagementService.setUserManagementServiceListener(managementListenerAdapter);
    Note: App developers are encouraged to use the ListenerAdapter implementations whenever possible as the Listener interfaces might get updated with new functionality/methods from one SDK release to the other. Therefore using a ListenerAdapter will make sure that there wont be any compilation issues due to unimplemented methods during a SDK upgrade.
